Ewart measured the pulse rate at some 130 per second with a frequency lying between 6 and 8 kHz. A recording of a specimen from north of Cooktown made by David Marshall (
Fig. 11
) showed a pulse rate of 120 per second with the majority of sound energy in the range 5–8 kHz with dominant frequencies between 6 and 6.5 kHz. Differences between the recordings of Ewart and Marshall are most likely due to differences in temperature (pulse rate) and individual variation (frequency).
